https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/pair-sum-in-a-sorted-and-rotated-array/0

Given an array of positive elements arr[] that is sorted and then rotated around an unknown point, the task is to check if the array has a pair with sum equals to a given target.

Below is my solution for the above questions with all 1112 / 1112 test case passed.


class Solution {
    static boolean pairInSortedRotated(int arr[], int target) {
        // Your code here
        Arrays.sort(arr);
        boolean found=false;
        int left = 0;
        int right = arr.length-1;
        while(left<right){
            int sum = arr[left]+arr[right];
            if(sum == target){
                found=true;
                break;
            }
            if(sum<target){
                left++;
            }
            else{
                right--;
            }
        }
        return found;
    }
}
